OL,6,FBuzzcocks frontman Pete Shelley was
OL,7,Fthe 'catalyst' to a music revolution
OL,8,Fduring the 80s, a new book has claimed.
OL,10,FPaul Hanley, author of 'Sixteen Again:
OL,11,FHow Pete Shelley & Buzzcocks Changed
OL,12,FManchester Music (and me)', believes
OL,13,FShelley and the punk band Buzzcocks
OL,14,Fwere vital to the musical
OL,15,Ftransformation during the 80s in .
OL,17,FWith the book released on what would
OL,18,Fhave been Shelley's 69th birthday, 17
OL,19,FApril, Paul feels the Buzzcocks do not
OL,20,Freceive enough credit for their
OL,21,Fcultural impact to the city.
